HEADWORD: Acrolith
<hw>Ac"ro*lith</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acrolthus</ets>, Gr. <grk>'akroli`qos</grk> with the ends made of
stone; <grk>'a`kros</grk> extreme + <grk>li`qos</grk> stone.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch. & Sculp.)</fld> <def>A statue whose extremities are of
stone, the trunk being generally of wood.</def>
<rj><au>Elmes.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

